RELATING TO TRANSPORTATION.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the State has been
2 struggling to expedite capital advancement projects that
3 increase harbor resilience and operational efficiency. The
4 department of transportation is authorized to enter into capital
5 advancement contracts with private parties for any public
6 improvement to, or construction of, a state harbor facility if
7 the director of transportation determines that the contract
8 promotes the best interest of the State and meets certain
9 requirements.
10 The legislature further finds that the fiscal caps on
11 capital advancement projects limit the scope, type of work, and
12 number of projects that can be executed under such contracts.
13 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to:
14 (1) Increase the maximum value of capital advancement
15 contracts that may be executed by the department of
16 transportation without legislative approval;
